<emphasis box="[710,803,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="585">jefersoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Comellini" authorityName="Comellini" box="[953,1201,1865,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Metopiasoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandior">
<emphasis box="[953,975,1866,1889]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="585">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[991,1085,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="585">grandior</emphasis>
Comellini
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1273,1357,1866,1889]" name="Panama" pageId="0" pageNumber="585">Panama</collectingCountry>
(Cerro Colorado), in having the posterolateral margin of the head with a cone-like prolongation (
<figureCitation box="[1145,1208,1901,1924]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="585">
Fig. 
<number box="[1198,1208,1901,1924]" pageId="0" pageNumber="585" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A,C). 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Metopiasoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jefersoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="585">Metopiasoides jefersoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the medioapical emargination of sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[959,1019,1936,1959]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="585">
Fig. 
<number box="[1009,1019,1936,1959]" pageId="0" pageNumber="585" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
H) and the shape of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="585">
