<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="587" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1665]" box="[199,1377,152,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,152,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[344,443,152,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Holotype</typeStatus>
male, BL: 
<number box="[563,613,152,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="5.19">5.19</number>
. Body, mouthparts, antennae and tarsi reddish dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1246,1305,152,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[1296,1305,152,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A–D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1665]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Head: pyriform (
<figureCitation box="[383,444,186,209]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[435,444,186,209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C–D), longer (HL: 
<number box="[661,709,186,209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.86">0.86</number>
) than wide (HW: 
<number box="[910,960,186,209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.68">0.68</number>
), anterior region distinctly narrower ending and slightly raised apically at the antennal tubercle. Posterior margin of head abruptly narrowing and with a small conelike projection at the posteriolateral angles. Neck almost half width of head and with margins rounded. Head with two vertexal foveae [vf] (
<figureCitation box="[384,446,290,313]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[436,446,290,313]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C) near posterior margin, connected by transverse sulcus. Vertex longitudinally impressed with a shallow sulcus running from anterior margin of antennal tubercle to neck. Ventral surface of head (
<figureCitation box="[1288,1349,325,348]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[1339,1349,325,348]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D) with long gular sulcus widening towards neck, interrupted in the posterior third by two gular foveae [gf] connected by a curved sulcus. Eyes (
<figureCitation box="[376,434,394,417]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[425,434,394,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C–D) prominent, situated at middle of head length and directed anteriorly. Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[1349,1408,394,417]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[1398,1408,394,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F) 
<number box="[151,165,429,452]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[173,185,429,452]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="3.0">3</number>
of length of body, scape almost half antenna length, last three antennomeres gradually broadening. Scape length 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" unit="mm" value="1.55">1.55 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[272,368,464,487]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" unit="mm" value="0.11">0.11 mm</quantity>
, pedicel shorter than scape (
<number box="[668,716,464,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.22">0.22</number>
: 
<number box="[736,786,464,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.09">0.09</number>
), antennomere 
