: 
<number box="[1044,1092,464,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.09">0.09</number>
) longer than wide, antennomere 
<number box="[151,164,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<number box="[178,226,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.18">0.18</number>
: 
<number box="[247,295,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.09">0.09</number>
) longer than wide, antennomere 
<number box="[646,659,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="5.0">5</number>
(
<number box="[674,722,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.14">0.14</number>
: 
<number box="[743,791,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.1">0.10</number>
) longer than wide, antennomere 
<number box="[1142,1155,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="6.0">6</number>
(
<number box="[1170,1217,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.11">0.11</number>
: 
<number box="[1238,1286,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.1">0.10</number>
) subquadrate, antennomere 
<number box="[296,309,533,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="7.0">7</number>
(
<number box="[324,371,533,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.11">0.11</number>
: 
<number box="[393,441,533,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.1">0.10</number>
) subquadrate, antennomere 
<number box="[743,756,533,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<number box="[771,819,533,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.1">0.10</number>
: 
<number box="[841,889,533,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.1">0.10</number>
) quadrate, antennomere 
<number box="[1154,1167,533,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="9.0">9</number>
(
<number box="[1182,1230,533,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.15">0.15</number>
: 
<number box="[1252,1299,533,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.11">0.11</number>
) longer than wide, antennomere 
<number box="[363,390,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="10.0">10</number>
(
<number box="[405,453,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.14">0.14</number>
: 
<number box="[476,523,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.11">0.11</number>
) longer than wide, antennomere 
<number box="[880,906,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="11.0">11</number>
(
<number box="[921,969,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.27">0.27</number>
: 
<number box="[993,1041,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.09">0.09</number>
) longer than wide; all antennomeres covered by long microsetae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1665]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Thorax: pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[420,486,637,660]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[476,486,637,660]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C) wider than long (PL: 
<number box="[781,831,637,660]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.6">0.60</number>
; PW: 
<number box="[907,955,637,660]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="0.72">0.72</number>
) with a weak median longitudinal sulcus. Pronotum convex with apices produced into acute projections, lateral margin to a deep transverse sulcus at half pronotum length. Pronotum with a slight transverse impression at base. Pronotal basal margin concave. Prosternum with lateral procoxal fovea [lpcf]. Mesoventrite with prepectal fovea [ppf] and lateral mesosternal fovea [lmsf]. External margin of mesocoxal cavities with lateral mesocoxal foveae [lmcf]. Metaventrite with two pointed tubercles in the middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1665]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Elytra: wider than long (EL: 
<number box="[527,577,810,833]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.08">1.08</number>
; EW: 
<number box="[650,700,810,833]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.2">1.20</number>
), sides gradually broadening apically (
<figureCitation box="[1131,1195,810,833]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[1185,1195,810,833]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Posterior margins concave, humeri with an obtuse tubercular swelling and sutural stria [ss] present. Elytron with two basal elytral foveae [bef] at anterior margin, one close to the elytral suture, while the second is smaller and located near the middle of elytral width at base. Apical-lateral margin of elytra distinctly notched. Flight wings (
<figureCitation box="[985,1044,914,937]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[1035,1044,914,937]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A–B) well developed, three times as long as elytra when fully extended and covered by minute setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1665]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Legs: Legs long and slender. Femora thickened in apical half. Tibiae curved and similar in length to femora, all tibiae thickened at apex. Protibiae lacking microsetae on the concave, mesial face, which is carinate. Tarsi 
<number box="[1293,1304,1018,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="3.0">3</number>
-segmented, first tarsomeres very short and last 
<number box="[522,535,1053,1076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="2.0">2</number>
tarsomeres longer, tarsomere 
<number box="[853,866,1053,1076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="2.0">2</number>
longer that segment 
<number box="[1088,1103,1053,1076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="3.0">3</number>
; all tarsi with a single claw and a minute accessory seta.Procoxae, mesocoxae conical and prominent, metacoxae transverse, region that articulates with the trochanter conical shaped. Procoxae with small prosternal process apically pointed, mesocoxae widely separated, metacoxae contiguous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1665]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Abdomen: strongly marginated, with five visible tergites (morphological tergites IV–VIII), tergite III reduced to small plate under elytra, tergite VIII with rounded apex. Tergites IV–VII bordered by distinct paratergites. Sternite III with transversal depressed plate completely nude and placed under the metacoxae, this transversal plate have a longitudinal projected carina in the middle. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[767,827,1296,1319]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[817,827,1296,1319]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
H) widely emarginated at apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1665]" box="[199,1258,1330,1353]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Aedeagus: asymmetric with the parameres fused, median lobe slightly bulbous at base (
<figureCitation box="[1132,1195,1330,1353]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[1182,1195,1330,1353]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
J–L).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1665]" box="[199,405,1364,1388]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis box="[199,279,1364,1388]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1665]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1400,1423]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Habitat.</emphasis>
The specimen was collected in the Peruvian Amazon forest at Urubamba Valley (at an altitude of 
<number box="[1382,1435,1400,1423]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="2035.0">2035</number>
meters).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,726,1469,1492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1665]" box="[199,726,1469,1492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1469,1492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[588,634,1469,1492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="587" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1665]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1504,1527]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in honor to my friend and colleague Jeferson Suarez 
<collectingCountry box="[1153,1184,1504,1527]" name="South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">De</collectingCountry>
la Cruz, who collected the specimen and work at the 
<collectionCode box="[469,554,1538,1561]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">MUSM</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="587" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1665]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,329,1573,1596]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Comments.</emphasis>
The new species belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[740,895,1572,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Metopiasoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[740,895,1572,1596]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">Metopiasoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the relative size of the third antennomere (
<figureCitation box="[159,218,1608,1631]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[208,218,1608,1631]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F), which is longer than the second and fourth antennomeres. The second and fourth antennal segments are similar in length and width. The mesial face of the protibia (
<figureCitation box="[711,771,1642,1665]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,205,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[153,1434,191,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metopiasoides jefersoni new species, holotype, A, habitus, dorsal view: B, habitus, left lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, head, ventral view; E, first leg; F, right antenna, lateral view; G, Tergum VIII (T 8); H, Sternum VIII (S 8); I, tergum IX (T 9), lateral view; J, aedeagus, ventral view; K, aedeagus, lateral view; L, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: A – B, 1 mm; C – F, 0.5 mm; G – L, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262189/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[761,771,1642,1665]" pageId="2" pageNumber="587" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
E) is carinate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
